\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 with spin 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma$
\end_inset

 to a state 
\begin_inset Formula $\tilde{\tilde{\beta}}$
\end_inset

 at site 
\begin_inset Formula $j$
\end_inset

 with spin 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma^{\prime}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $t_{\alpha\beta}=\langle\tilde{\tilde{\alpha}}\sigma i|\mathcal{H}_{\text{R}}|\tilde{\tilde{\beta}}\sigma^{\prime}j\rangle$
\end_inset

.
 Notice that, using the tilde hat notation, we specify that both the site
 and spin indices were removed taken from all the other possible generic
 degrees of freedom (thus 1 tilde for 1 degree of freedom specified), 
\begin_inset Formula $|\alpha\rangle\equiv|\tilde{\tilde{\alpha}}\sigma i\rangle=|\tilde{\tilde{\alpha}}\rangle\otimes|\sigma\rangle\otimes|i\rangle$
\end_inset

.
 This notation will be used throughout the notes, so that 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

